76561198025440912,Not Recommended,297000,14269783,"Posted: 31 January, 2015",all,maktgalena,"While I absolutely love the original game, which I´ve played since the release, this HD remake is quite a disappointment for several reasons:1. The graphics look like they were only scaled up and smoothed out. Meaning parts look blurry, lacking in detail, and horrible black borders around characters.2. The colours seem to have been oversaturated in the process, making your eyes tired and sting when looking at the screen.3. The animation is painful to watch. Agreed, the original animation was not beautiful or smooth, but I expected that the movements might have been smoothed out - Instead they are choppier and clumsier than ever.4. There is no random map feature... which is what made the original game playable for 16 years.5. E...ver...y...thing... Is... So. Slow. I play Dragon Age 3 on the highest graphic settings without any issues, but this HOMM3 HD remake lags as if I was playing online with a 64kbps connection.6. Features missing, like for example hotkeys. I´ve always played this game using hotkeys, but now they can´t be used.7. Online multiplayer doesn´t work. The multiplayer functionality is one of the main reasons I bought the game, as it is cumbersome to try and set up the kind of networks that the original one needs to work, but now it feels like I wasted 15 euros on this game.TL;DRAs I loved the original game to bits I obviously had very high hopes for this remake, and I am sad to say that this version does not live up to the original and is not worth the 15 euros it costs. My recommendation is to seek out the original game and play that instead."
