,Recommended,297000,28657819,"Posted: 25 December, 2016",all,Syncourt,"The best in the series and an all-round classic.HOMM3 continues to display it's perfection even decades after it's creation. Many turn based strategy games only wish they could be as big as this one is. What makes this game amazing is it's army and unit diversity, each being visually and tactically unique, effective and fun. The simple mechanics behind the game make it very easy to learn while keeping turns quick which really helps the flow of the game in multiplayer.While the campaign mode is great on it's own, one of the best things about HOMM3 is it's 8 player multiplayer and infinite supply of randomly generated or user created maps. This HOMM3 HD does not actually include the map generator itself, but there are workarounds to get it working with this and guides to download a large number of the maps online. Mutiplayer can be played over LAN, Online and even hot seat on the single PC (great for when friends visit).The largest downside to HOMM3 HD is the lack of HOMM3 expansions. After decades of playing with the expansions it feels like a decent chunk of the game is missing. Those who have never played the original would not notice the difference though and realistically, there isn't actually that much missing.The newer HOMM games could all learn a thing or two from this one. This game was never about how stunning it looked, it was all about how much content it had and how well it played. The game didn't need to sell the armies to you in DLC chunks, people got them mainly just for the campaign and story alone. The game is well optimized for performance, never crashed and was mostly bug free. The AI armies could use a little work but AI wasn't really that advanced back then.Overall this is a great remake of the original HOMM3 but it is not really necessary to enjoy the game, the main attractions are just the visual improvements and being easier to set up online play. Without the expansions you would need to weigh up if that is worth sacrificing the expansions additional content for.Things I really enjoy about this game:Well written lore and story.Army and unit diversity.Infinite supply of random/user generated maps.Not overly complicated. Turns are fast.Hero skill customisation options allow for different playstyles.RPG mechanics allow you to make your heroes stronger and alter thier combat focus as the game progresses.Perfectly optimized and near entirely bug free.Great multiplayer.Can play hotseat on a single PC.Things I really dislike about this game:The only thing I really dislike about this game is the lack of expansion content."
