,Recommended,297000,14701470,"Posted: 28 February, 2015",all,weezact7,"Let me start by saying that there is a caveat to my recommendation of this game, but more on that in a minute. First, the game itself.Heroes 3 is, in my opinion, the best game of the series by a wide margin. It's tight, well-balanced, and offers lots of replay value with the map editor. If you've never played this game and you like strategy games, pick it up. You won't be sorry. Having it on steam makes it even easier to play with friends and, hopefully, will bring a good pool of custom maps from the community.That being said, this is only the base game. You can buy this PLUS two expansion sets for $10 on another website (the URL escapes me for the moment). This adds a new town type and a random map generator. Some people really like these features, I find them trivial. But it's still more stuff for less money. On the downside, you lose that steam compatibility aspect.So, do I recommend getting this? Yes. Do I think it's worth $15? No. If you're like me and $15 is chump change, get it anyway. If $15 is a lot of money for you or you can't justify spending more money on a game than it's worth, wait for a sale and get it 50% off or something. It's not like you'll have to wait long. Steam does them often enough."
