,Recommended,297000,15238949,"Posted: 6 April, 2015",all,Crafty Ape,"Ignore the naysayers. As someone who plays his PC games on a 40"" screen, this HD version was necessary and greatly appreciated.Heroes III is one of my favourite games of all time, and easily my favourite strategy game. I've been playing it since I was 6 or 7 and never really stopped but in recent years, along with upgrading to bigger and higher reslolution screens, the games visuals increasingly looked pixellated and basically pretty damn ugly.I tried the unofficial HD mod but all that really did was increase the interface size and did very little for the actual textures themselves. Now with this HD version, the game looks beautiful and so it's as good as it's ever been.Are there flaws? Well yes. It doesn't include the expansions, the battles are still in 4:3 ratio (with borders) and a few of the repainted models look a bit derpy (I'm looking at you wood elves). But truly, this is a small price to pay for an old  game to look absolutely stunning. This breathes life in one of the best turn-based strategy games ever made.However I would appreciate it if Ubisoft added the expansions as DLC. And because of the price point I can see why people would rather just stick to the original version which you can get on GOG for a small fraction of the price of this HD version. My advice to you is to look at your monitor size. If it's 1080p and bigger than, say, 24"", then I recommend getting the HD version all day. Either way you can't really go wrong. Heroes III is still Heroes III."
