,Recommended,297000,14430183,"Posted: 11 February, 2015",all,frostbytes89,"You know what's really sad.. in 1999 3DO released Heroes of Might and Magic III. I played that game for _years_. Not only have I been playing it since I was around 9 years old, I've probably put thousands of hours into it altogether.That said, I have never seen a single bug. I'm not saying that they don't exist, but they sure as hell were not obvious. The game was so polished that to this day it remains the iconic and definitive version of the HOMM series.As we know, Ubisoft has done a remake of the game in HD. They claim to have repolished some 20k+ assets. I've played about 11 hours (according to steam) and in those 11 hours have noticed blatant, unacceptable, almost laughable bugs. Its so amazing what damage can be done to a product when the motive behind producing it is money, instead of the gratification of doing a good job and being proud of what you get to share with people.Example bugs:1. I went to move my battle dwarf, and instead of the battle dwarf moving sound, it played the death sound from an enemy unit I recently killed, _every_ _single_ _step_. And it wasn't just my dwarf! When the enemy moved his it played the same sound! Its as if the data got mixed up somehow. Maybe a dangling pointer? In any case, certainly no excuse for it considering the original never exposed an issue like that.2. These ""HD"" ground clutter sprites frequently bug out and cause the grid to be able to be highlighted and its color change to that of a valid state, as if you could move there. The old version correctly changed to the ""cannot move there"" cursor - every time.3. The game flat out stops when it receives WM_KILLFOCUS from the Windows message pump. Not ""stops rendering"" or ""stops audio"". I mean the game stops. It pauses everything. So you can't end your turn and do something else while the AI runs their turn. You can't even click on your castle and alt tab out to load a youtube video or something. Granted, not a bug, but totally unnecessary change.4.Arbitrary extremely weird glitches like a unit just jumping places for no reason and moving back.It just overall feels unpolished, untested, and unfinished. It was clearly released because after every single HOMM release since HOMM5, ubisoft has been flooded with comments from HOMM players expressing how far they have deviated from Heroes III and how they should just make that but updated.Well, Ubisoft did it. I still play it because the bugs aren't game breaking, its easy for me to run and keep game states, and its a good game that 3DO made. Its still fun despite the bugs! I feel like they took a group of intern artists for 6 months to do all the assets, and then a few engineers spent a couple months porting it over. Other than that, no love was given to the polish of the game. I get all happy when I load it up, but then just kind of frown inside and go ""..okay.. thanks for this I guess I'll take it.."" as I load up a map."
