76561198009592080,Recommended,297000,14220497,"Posted: 28 January, 2015",all,fryet7,"Update:  I changed my review from negative to positive after 2 hours of play.  You can see the old review below.  The music is the same between original and HD release.  There are 4 combat soundtracks, and 3 is the annoying one.  It isn't that annoying if the sound is turned down some.  Once I had similar sound levels between computers, they sounded identical.  While I haven't seen all units yet, the only one that I consider worse than the original is the pikeman.  The rest seem fine to me.Here is the old review:This is my first impression after playing for 20 minutes.  I have a KVM setup so I can switch between the old version on a Windows XP machine, and the new version on Windows 7, viewing both on the same monitor.My first impression was positive.  The initial screens looked better and more crisp.  The color palette is the same, bright colors that made the original artwork charming.  I then navigated to the combat screen, and that is where I went to a negative rating for the game.  The art for the pikeman was pretty bad.  The archer was ok, and I didn't notice anything glaringly bad about the enemies I was facing.What I found really annoying was the combat music.  On the original version, the music had deeper tones and a good pace.  On the new version, it was this annoying high pitched instrument (flute maybe?).  The pace seemed slightly faster too, making me feel agitated.  Considering that you hear the combat music over and over in this game, bad music can get very annoying.  I am trying to decide if the newer graphics are worth the bad music.  I think my initial feeling is that I would rather play the original.On the positive, this is supported for Windows 7, so if my XP machine dies, at least I have an option to continue playing it.P.S.  The intro video did not appear updated.  I am not surprised, as it would have been a major undertaking for little value."
