,Recommended,297000,32334568,Posted: 10 June,all,Lycan,"This game is simple. Manage a kingdom in a turn based, board game type style in a beautiful landscape while building an army in order to crush your enemies in different scenarios. Easily one of my favorite childhood games and still a favorite to this day. Atmosphere and soundtrack are also really good since the overworld music is nice, quiet, and calm. Whereas battle music is fast paced and heavy. The different kingdoms to choose from also offer a good variety so you arent constantly making the same army over and over again. While not the best version of HoMM3 since you can get the same game but with expansions fromGOG.com, this game is still dope. It may seem slow at times and might take you a bit to get into but its amazing especially with friends since you start to plan more on how to manage your kingdom/army while plotting to get rid of other kingdoms. The GOG version is also cheaper but to play with friends you will all need Gameranger and will have to set up games with that. But if you dont wanna go through all of that (even though it isnt a lot) then just buy the steam version.so all in all-GOG.com'sversion is cheaper and comes with expansions but online requires Gameranger and isn't in hd (i believe)BUT- the game is in hd- the online is easy and fast as hell to set up with friends- there arent any bugs or game breaking glitches from which i have seen"
